title Risk Management in Financial Services
style wardley

// Anchors — three distinct user / demand types
anchor Public [0.98, 0.55]
anchor Corporations [0.97, 0.60]
anchor Governments [0.96, 0.50]

// Society / accountability layer (above providers in the accountability chain)
component Society Accountability [0.90, 0.35]
component Trust [0.88, 0.40]

// Providers — the delivery layer customers see
component Retail Banking [0.82, 0.78]
component Insurance [0.80, 0.65]
component Lending [0.78, 0.70]

// Trust-and-assets bridge connecting providers to customers
component Assets Under Management [0.72, 0.60]
component Customer Trust Layer [0.74, 0.45]
component Identity and KYC [0.68, 0.72]

// Oversight / shaping forces acting on providers
component Regulation [0.65, 0.38]
component Rating Agencies [0.62, 0.70]
component Sovereignty Concerns [0.60, 0.25]

// Risk types the map is meant to surface
component Credit Risk [0.55, 0.78]
component Systemic Risk [0.52, 0.45]
component Cybersecurity Risk [0.50, 0.55]
component Cascade Failure Risk [0.46, 0.30]
component Third-Party Risk [0.44, 0.42]

// Cross-cutting concepts the scenario calls out on the evolution axis
component Cost [0.38, 0.82]
component Value [0.36, 0.40]
component Supply Chain Awareness [0.30, 0.28]

// Supporting data / infrastructure
component Risk Models [0.28, 0.50]
component Transaction Data [0.22, 0.80]
component Core Banking Platform [0.18, 0.70]
component Cloud Infrastructure [0.12, 0.90]
component Payment Rails [0.10, 0.88]

// Demand edges — anchors to providers
Public->Retail Banking
Public->Insurance
Public->Lending
Corporations->Retail Banking
Corporations->Insurance
Corporations->Lending
Governments->Regulation
Governments->Sovereignty Concerns
Governments->Insurance

// Accountability chain back to society
Society Accountability->Regulation
Society Accountability->Trust
Trust->Customer Trust Layer
Public->Trust
Corporations->Trust

// Providers to trust-and-assets bridge
Retail Banking->Assets Under Management
Retail Banking->Customer Trust Layer
Retail Banking->Identity and KYC
Insurance->Assets Under Management
Insurance->Customer Trust Layer
Lending->Assets Under Management
Lending->Identity and KYC
Lending->Customer Trust Layer

// Oversight shaping providers
Regulation->Retail Banking
Regulation->Insurance
Regulation->Lending
Rating Agencies->Lending
Rating Agencies->Insurance
Sovereignty Concerns->Regulation
Sovereignty Concerns->Cloud Infrastructure

// Risks attach to provider surfaces (a provider "depends on" managing each risk)
Retail Banking->Credit Risk
Lending->Credit Risk
Insurance->Systemic Risk
Retail Banking->Systemic Risk
Retail Banking->Cybersecurity Risk
Insurance->Cybersecurity Risk
Lending->Cybersecurity Risk
Retail Banking->Cascade Failure Risk
Insurance->Cascade Failure Risk
Retail Banking->Third-Party Risk
Insurance->Third-Party Risk
Lending->Third-Party Risk

// Risks and cross-cutting concepts
Credit Risk->Risk Models
Systemic Risk->Risk Models
Cybersecurity Risk->Cloud Infrastructure
Cascade Failure Risk->Supply Chain Awareness
Third-Party Risk->Supply Chain Awareness
Third-Party Risk->Cloud Infrastructure

// Cost / Value / Trust / Supply-chain awareness placement on evolution axis
Retail Banking->Cost
Retail Banking->Value
Insurance->Cost
Insurance->Value
Lending->Cost
Lending->Value
Customer Trust Layer->Value
Trust->Value

// Data / infrastructure
Risk Models->Transaction Data
Identity and KYC->Core Banking Platform
Assets Under Management->Core Banking Platform
Core Banking Platform->Cloud Infrastructure
Core Banking Platform->Payment Rails
Transaction Data->Cloud Infrastructure

// Regulation-lagging-risk inertia: regulation is less evolved than the risks it covers
component Regulation [0.65, 0.38] inertia
// 17-forms inertia note: "political capital" + "existing practice" resist regulatory evolution.

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast)
evolve Cybersecurity Risk 0.75
evolve Third-Party Risk 0.60
evolve Supply Chain Awareness 0.55
evolve Regulation 0.55

// Strategic notes
note Regulation lagging the risks it covers [0.66, 0.55]
note High differentiation zone [0.70, 0.25]
note Utility / outsource candidates [0.15, 0.90]
